A new examination has just
been announced for filling Treas
ury Enforcement Agent positions
in ten western states with the
Bureau of Customs, Bureau of
Marc otics, Secret Service, and
the Internal Revenue Service.
Successful candidates will inves-
tigate criminal cases involving
violations of Federal laws within
the enforcement jurisdiction of
the Treasury Department. En-
trance salaries are $4,000 to
$5795 year.


Further information may be
obtained at most post offices or
from the Board of U. S. Civil
Service Examiners, Internal

WASHINGTON State Deaprt-
ment officials said during De-
cember and January at least IL
African students left the Soviet
Union to continue education in
the west.


They also said there Is a con-
slant trickle Of African and other
foreign students out Of Com
munist countries and through a
West German reception center
which seeks placement else
where. They estimated the rate
at 10 to IL a month.

NEW YORK CITY -"Charm by
Choice" a 14-minute sound and
color filmslide, released re-
Gently by the National Urban
League as a part of its Educa-
ton and Youth Incentives pro-
gram, is the first of its kind
produced by a non-profit agency.


The filmslide has direct ap-
peal to a rnulti-racial audience.
Its models are girls Of varied
racial and ethnic backgr ounds.
Ways Of obtaining good groom
ing on a limited budget are shown.


Companion pieces in the film
slide kit. are a Teacher 9
Guide" and a Beauty and Charm
Checklist for a girl to carry
in her purse as a daily reminder
Of the necessary essentials that
go into good grooming.


Otis E. Finley. Jr., associate
director of the National Urban
League, said: "This filmslide
Is the result Of many requests
from local Urban Leagues,
schools. and building
agencies for visual aid to help
young girls. and particularly Ne
gro girls, develop self-pride and
confidence through personal care
and good grooming. The transit
tion from the classroom to the
world Of work is frequently a diff
hcult one" he continued, "and
we believe this filmslide will fill
a tremendous gap in the guidance
materials available for young
women
